South Africans will have a front row seat for the wedding of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle in May. ITV Choice (DStv 123) will do a live broadcast of the royal ceremony on May 19 from 10.25am until 4pm. It will be hosted by Julie Etchingham and Phillip Schofield who will be joined by a team of reporters and a range of guests including those who know Prince Harry and Meghan. Rageh Omaar meanwhile will join Sentebale‚ the charity co-founded by Prince Harry‚ for traditional wedding day celebrations in Lesotho. He will be live from the Mamohato Children’s Centre where he will be joined by beneficiaries and staff‚ many of whom have met and been supported by Prince Harry during his numerous visits to the country.